Sure the place is pretty ratty and disorganized but I think the front office does the best they can with what they've got.  The wait time is pretty gruesome, the waiting room is pretty small and it is a very busy practice.  But you get what you pay for.  The receptionist, Desiree (sp?) may not be the best at customer service but she probably has the most stressful position there!  answering phones, checking people in, data entry and everyone seems to be talking to her at once and needing something from her.!  The office manager, Veronica, went above and beyond to help us wade through the amount of dental work my husband needed and how we were going to finance it.

<review>Everyone loves this place for a good reason. Their food is delicious. Their pupusas are the best. They have a special on Monday and Friday pupusas for a dollar. Their pupusas are regularly $2.00 and their cheese with loroco pupusas are $2.20. Their prices are super great. Did I mention their portion size? Well it's a huge portion of food. It's a cozy restaurant that you'll enjoy sitting for a comfortable meal. The huevos rancheros plate is amazing. Every single one of their plates is huge so come with an appetite. My favorite is the green beans and eggs plate. The platano Fritos are just perfect. If you like licuados their strawberry licuado is a must. I always get a pupusas because it's the reason why my family found this place.

Their customer service is amazing. The ladies are super attentive. Everything is made on the spot. So don't think you'll get your food as fast as MacDonald's. I recommend this place to everyone.</review>< Resp>

< date>
1548047353517< /date>
<Text>In 2014, I took my son, a third grader, to get an orthodontic evaluation. During the consultation, Dr. Nicole pointed out my son long chin. Of course as a mom, I seen nothing wrong with my son. She ordered a lateral x-ray of his face. While my son was out of the room, Dr. Nicole preceded to ask me questions about my son; does he wake up often during the night? Does he have allergies? The questions continued, I stopped listening to her questions and focused on the past.

My eyes filled with tears, as she showed my son's lateral x-ray. His adenoids were enlarged pushing his chin downward & causing to block his airway.

Your probably wondering why I was so emotional. When my son was 2yrs old, after a week of being hospitalized, it took five doctors to come to a conclusion & diagnose my son with asthma. After his diagnosis, the hospital became our second home. He had a lot of asthma flare-ups. Almost every pulmonary x-rays were clear. He was given different medications. I am not sure if they even worked. I felt like the worst mom ever. Every time we visited the ER, I always felt attacked. My house looked like a pharmacy. One night, when I called 9-1-1 because my son was pale & having a hard time breathing. My son took a deep breath & yelled out to me "MOM! HELP ME! I NEED HELP! HELP ME MOM!" I cried uncontrollably because I wish I could take it all away. The paramedics got there and immediately gave him an epinephrine shot. He looked zoned out. That night he received two more epinephrine shots. Nothing was working. Again hospitalized. one occasion, I was asked to take a CPR class, just in case.

A few years of this routine, I was so upset. I yelled at the nurse, "this is ridiculous! We are always here! You guys make me feel like a bad mom! I'm doing everything you ask, and I am still here! THERE IS SOMETHING ELSE YOU GUYS ARE NOT DOING! So they ordered him an allergy test. After we got the results, we had to change our living conditions. Our house began to smell like cleaning products because he is allergic to dust & mold. We had to keep our pets outside. He was allergic dog & cat dander. I finally felt like something was getting done.

Boom! Another ER visit. What am I doing wrong? More tests were ordered. Many visits with the pulmonologist. I began to feel hopeless! The hospital bill's began to pile up. I was not working. My husband was in and out of jobs. Our financial situation was spiralling down. Obamacare was not ideal. Not qualify for medical, but had to chose between eating and getting my sons medication. Finally, my husband got a stable job & we were keeping up with mortgage. A few months later a blessing in disguise. My son teeth were so crooked. I felt we were financially stable to get him braces.

After our consultation, I got in my car & cried uncontrollably because Dr. Nicole had no idea what we have been through. This was my blessing. This was the prayer that was finally getting answered! After my son got his adenoids taken out, our lives, his life changed dramatically.

No more hospital visits. His medication was reduced or taken away. He read for a longer period of time. The list goes on, but the best part is that we can finally plan mini vacations without worry.

Getting my son's adenoids taken out, was the best thing that can ever happen to our lives. Thank you Dr. Nicole & the whole staff at Nalchajian Orthodontics!<//Text><userid>111296743838787703093< /userid><Rate>5< /Rate><username>Martha Mendoza</username></record>

Upon walking in, I tried to talk to an employee to find out where this item would be, and despite seeing multiple employees nearby the entrance, they all seemed to be actively walking away from me, uninterested in helping. When I finally cornered some employees (who still seemed like they didn't want to be interacting with me), I was pointed to the same wrong aisle on the complete wrong end of the store several times. It was only when I went to the garden section that a (reluctant) employee pointed me to the correct section.

Even in the appropriate section, though, options were scarce. Despite having dozens of planter boxes in stock, the only appropriate mounting brackets I could find had obviously been returned (one was disorganized in its packaging and was missing parts, and the other was literally in a gallon plastic bag) and were not labeled at all.

So in the end, I did get what I was looking for, but the store and its employees felt hostile to me at every turn. I don't normally complain about employee service because I recognize that people don't have to treat me like their master, but when several employees avoid to me and give me incorrect information and the product is shoddy and disorganized, I feel like I deserve to complain. < Review>
Wow! What an service!
Usually I don't have any preference for visiting Lowes or Home depot, but the recently experience I had with one of the associate here made me think about it.
Unlike other stores where we need to find the associate if we need an help, this guy came to me and ask if he can help me and even after helping me find the product, he was willing to wait and help me with other products too.

For one of the product which we were finding it difficult to locate, he pointed me towards another associate who had more expertise in that specific product, yet he didn't stop searching, he went out of his way to look for product while another associate was helping.

From now on, this store will definitely be my first choice over the another one.</Review>

< Text>
I only come here because it has parking and is not busy (The Home Depot had a 1 hour plus line, no line here). When they first opened Lowe's in the Bay area they were nice and organized, now they're really just disorganized dumps. <resp>None<//resp>< review>
While this is a very typical Lowe's, it's very hit and miss when it comes to service. Some days, I get amazing service - particularly in the Garden area and Lumber, but when it comes to Paint or picking up online order, it's been really awful lately.

One morning, a customer and myself waited 30 minutes for someone to come to the Paint department, and I cannot even tell you how how many employees walked right on by without a care that people were waiting.

In regards to online ordering, we use the service so it can expedite the process of getting what we need after a long day of work. So when you end up waiting longer than it would have taken to go get the items yourself, it doesn't make much sense. This Lowe's needs to figure out how to do the process better because Sunnyvale Lowe's is very quick and organized in comparison.

To top it all off, I STILL DON'T HAVE A DELIVERY SCHEDULED!!!!  This is a complete nightmare and I will never purchase anything from Lowe's again and will make sure to actively recommend to anyone I know to never order anything from Lowe's either if they can get the same thing elsewhere. <rating>5<//rating>< review>
I frequent many Lowe's / Home Depot and my experience here last night was amazing.

This store should be the model store for all Lowe's to follow.

Paint Section - My friend picked up paint and the worker actually asked what the paint is being used for.  She took the time to explain what texture is recommended and the difference between the prices.  Excellent!

Flooring Section - A worker came out of nowhere to ask if she could help and walked over to show where the items could be found.  Excellent!

Appliance Section - Jason came to help and took a lot of time to explain the many differences. When to buy to get the lowest price. Even showed the model rooms to show the newer colors and how certain sizes can look like.  He was very knowledgeable and really seemed to want to help!  Made recommendations and even mentioned which brands to stay away from.  Excellent!

Tools Section - Ian.  I don't know what he's doing here.  The guy should be running his own contractor business.  All I wanted to know was to know how to use my nail gun, but I walked out learning all the different uses for an air compressor.  Ian is VERY passionate about housing projects and it's very helpful to talk to him.  Super Excellent!

I never thought I'd say going to Lowe's was an amazing experience but this one really was!  Please give this one a try!</review>

< review>
While the staff in paint and plumbing were quite helpful and knowledgeable, there definitely aren't enough of them. But by far the worst part of my experience with Lowe's is with their installation department. I had scheduled an appointment to have a garbage disposal installed and was go liven an appointment window from 9-12am on a Monday. I scheduled the day off from work since I really needed this done and waited until 2pm for my installer to show up. Unfortunately I didn't realize that he had attempted to call me around 10am. I called Lowe's to make sure that my appointment would still be held and the woman in the installation department lied say "Oh it looks like you missed your appointment. My  technician called and waited for you for 20 minutes and then had to leave for another service appointment."
I informed her that that was not true; that I had been waiting at home all day and no one showed up. She then began to backtrack, saying that he was waiting for my call and because I hadn't called he hadn't shown up. Really?
No one told me that when I made the appointment! If I make an appointment with a client you better believe I show up even if they don't answer my call. So unprofessional! I was not offered an apology  or even a hint or remorse over the fact that my time had been wasted. Do yourself a favor and go to Home Depot instead!<//review>

After a long week and busy unproductive day off i settled down to BBQ. After getting a nice sear on one side the propane ran out around 9:15pm. Lowes has Blue Rhino 20lb tanks prefilled to 75% with 15lb for $15 exchange and  I'm off. Wait need gas and air up tires. Get to lowes 9:53 remove tank from rv. Head for the exit to enter because the registers are right there and you pay first after leaving empty tank by blue rhino cage. Cashier is free, no line, great. He turns around, sees me, and in  his matronly retail voice said, "We're closed," with distain.
I replied, i just need one thing, a tank of propane and i have my empty for exchange outside.
"I don't have a key and the other managers are busy doing their closing lists."
Big Mary is a manager! not just a cashier? You go gerl. He can remember his, I'm smart glasses, but not his propane key or how to be polite to customers who might be a little dirty at the end of a long day of home repairs utilising the plethora of items purchased from Lowes recently.
"I can call one of the "other" managers (the ones who didnt loose their Blue Rhino cage key) and have them unlock the cage if you would like. It might be a couple minutes, thought (ya ya they're busy with their closing lists, you covered that earlier. I may be tired, dirty and hungry but not stupid, condescending or rude. You will need to look in a mirror for an example of what those look like in combination) would have been acceptable. I know the store is closing and i rushed in late, because i was cooking late and ran out of propane late. Not because i was eating late on the summer continental schedule, but because i was working late like everyone here.
But this option was not offered and from the tone in his voice and the look i recieved as he turned his back to me walking to the exit door and wishing me in his "Dear God, please kill me, kill me now" retail voice, "Have a good evening" ("ba by" rang through loud and clear. I new without ramping things up to 11 i would not be getting any propane at Lowes and left. Home Depot is around the corner. I was going to race over and see if they would help me out. But, I was now more tired and just whent home.
For the record, i hope he is straight. The gay community has enough freaks in it allready.
Tonight, Thurs i stoped into the Lowes on Night Ridder in SJ and to add insult to injury the Blue Rhino 15 lb (25% empty. A 20 lb tank is rated for and designed to hold 20 lbs and it still has the governments reserve area for safe expansion preventing a failure) tank was now $19.99.
Two trips, a ruined dinner, dropped and broke the regulator when reloding tank into camper and a 25% price increase. Did i hear someone say OSH? I will continue to patronize Lowes. I have had more good experiences than dissapointing ones. The ratio between them is getting pretty flat and seems to be accelorating as it approaches 1:1.<//review>

<Review>I walk in the store and I'm in the need of a trailer. I've never purchased one before but I know what size I need. I see a 4x6 at the entrance but it's not the size I'm looking for. so 20 feet from the trailer I walk over to the cashier and ask if they have any other trailers I could look at. He tells me he doesn't know of any others. Standing in the same spot, in HIS line of site, I notice 2 other trailers sitting there. He didn't get my sarcasm, but I threw it his way anyways. "What about those?" I ask. With the dumbfounded look on his face he had nothing to say.
I walk over to the trailers and notice they're on sale and they are exactly what I was hoping for. I picked the better one of the two (one had broken light lenses). I go up to the check out desk to make the purchase but was told only 1 person in the store handles the DMV stuff. Of course, the person (John) wasn't there. She said he would be in in a bit. I asked her if he could call me when he got in, gave her my number and pleaded with her to PLEASE have him call me since we drove a distance to get this.
We tool around in the area for a few hours, no call from John. We go back to the store and when we pull in we see a fire truck, and an ambulance. i said out loud to my kids, "Watch, this will be thrown in my face!"
I go back to the desk (we're now over 3 hours into this) and I tell the person behind the counter we were expecting a call from John. Her reply, (with a healthy dose of attitude) "Well, you see what's  happening with the emergency vehicles out front, we've been a little busy!" And there it is... thrown in my face as I suspected. I wasn't rude or pushy, but may have had a slight bit of frustration in my demeanor as I was sympathetic to to whatever situation was brewing with the fire trucks. Apparently, John is also the only person who can handle emergencies, too!
4 hours into it, I'd yet to mean this Super John. finally, someone came up to assist us. I looked at the name tag and it said Juan. I thought maybe that was the John they were talking about. Then a few minutes later John walks up. I say nothing about the hours I've spent waiting for this transaction. Finally, hours later, we START the purchase. As I'm doing the paperwork I ask which one he is writing up, and noted that I wanted the one that didn't have broken lights. He said he picked the one he picked because the other had broken lights. Cool! I assumed we were on the same page.
Finally, about 5.5 hours from when I arrived at the store, we're done. I ask how the paperwork is handled with the DMV. He specifically told me that LOWE's would take care of all that and that I would receive the plates in the mail from the DMV. I confirm, "I don't have to do anything else, and they plates will be sent to me?" "Yep!' he says.
They tell me to meet them at the back of the store, at the back door where the trailer is parked and they will be right there. I drive around, wait 10 minutes, 10 minutes longer, then finally i see movement. Out comes the trailer. As we're attaching it to my hitch, I notice the light lens is broke. He tries to right the situation by grabbing a new lens and putting it on, which was nice. As he's walking away I notice one of the marker lights is also cracked open. I just wanted to get the hell out of that place! I didn't say anything about the 2nd light.
I wait a couple of months for the plates, but get nothing. I read the paperwork and it says it takes a while, and to call DMV if you haven't received the plates in 60 days. Well, i gave it LOTS of extra time... 5 months to be exact! So finally I call DMV. I give them the VIN number only to find it's not in their system. She asks me what paperwork I'm looking at. When I tell her, she is able to quickly decipher that Lowe's gave me completely wrong information. I was supposed to go to the DMV and bring the paperwork so they could register it in their system.
This place simply sucks!< /Review>< gmap_id>
